From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000012 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Boot Debug <noreply@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [DEBUG] refpolicy: allow systemd/udev to write tracefs (BOOTPROF)

The BOOTPROF instrumentation writes ftrace markers to
/sys/kernel/tracing/trace_marker from systemd (init_t) and udevd (udev_t).
Under SELinux enforcing these writes are denied, so no markers are recorded.

Adds a minimal refpolicy module 'qcom_bootprof' allowing init_t and udev_t
to open/write tracefs files and search tracefs dirs. Ships the full refpolicy
trio -- .te (rules), .if (empty interface summary, needed by the doc build),
.fc (empty file-contexts, needed by the .pp module build) -- plus a
modules.conf append. Wired into the refpolicy-targeted bbappend SRC_URI after
the nhx module (shares modules.conf, so must apply after it). Debug-only;
drop this entry from local-patches.yml to restore stock policy.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [debug instrumentation]
---
diff --git a/dynamic-layers/selinux/recipes-security/refpolicy/refpolicy-targeted/0002-Add-SELinux-policy-for-bootprof-tracefs.patch b/dynamic-layers/selinux/recipes-security/refpolicy/refpolicy-targeted/0002-Add-SELinux-policy-for-bootprof-tracefs.patch
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..09216621
--- /dev/null
+++ b/dynamic-layers/selinux/recipes-security/refpolicy/refpolicy-targeted/0002-Add-SELinux-policy-for-bootprof-tracefs.patch
@@ -0,0 +1,91 @@
+From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000002 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: Boot Debug <noreply@qti.qualcomm.com>
+Date: Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
+Subject: [PATCH] Add SELinux policy for BOOTPROF tracefs marker writes
+
+The BOOTPROF boot-time instrumentation makes systemd (init_t) and udevd
+(udev_t) write ftrace markers to /sys/kernel/tracing/trace_marker. Under
+SELinux enforcing these writes are denied (tclass=file, tcontext=tracefs_t),
+so no markers are recorded.
+
+Add a minimal policy module 'qcom_bootprof' that allows init_t and udev_t
+to open/write tracefs files and search tracefs directories. Ships the full
+.te/.if/.fc trio (the .if and .fc are minimal, as the module only adds allow
+rules and labels no files) so refpolicy's module build succeeds. Debug-only:
+drop this module to restore stock policy.
+
+Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [debug instrumentation]
+
+Signed-off-by: Boot Debug <noreply@qti.qualcomm.com>
+---
+ policy/modules.conf                      |  6 ++++++
+ policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.fc |  1 +
+ policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.if |  4 ++++
+ policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.te | 21 +++++++++++++++++++++
+ 4 files changed, 32 insertions(+)
+ create mode 100644 policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.fc
+ create mode 100644 policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.if
+ create mode 100644 policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.te
+
+diff --git a/policy/modules.conf b/policy/modules.conf
+index 1111111..2222222 100644
+--- a/policy/modules.conf
++++ b/policy/modules.conf
+@@ -1,6 +1,12 @@
+ # Layer: services
+ # Module: qcom_nhx
+ #
+ # Qualcomm NHX camera test launcher
+ #
+ qcom_nhx = module
++
++# Layer: services
++# Module: qcom_bootprof
++#
++# BOOTPROF tracefs marker access for systemd/udev
++#
++qcom_bootprof = module
+diff --git a/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.fc b/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.fc
+new file mode 100644
+index 0000000..5555555
+--- /dev/null
++++ b/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.fc
+@@ -0,0 +1 @@
++# qcom_bootprof: no file contexts (allow-only module)
+diff --git a/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.if b/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.if
+new file mode 100644
+index 0000000..3333333
+--- /dev/null
++++ b/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.if
+@@ -0,0 +1,4 @@
++## <summary>
++## BOOTPROF: allow systemd/udev to write ftrace trace_marker under tracefs.
++## Debug-only instrumentation module; no callable interfaces.
++## </summary>
+diff --git a/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.te b/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.te
+new file mode 100644
+index 0000000..4444444
+--- /dev/null
++++ b/policy/modules/services/qcom_bootprof.te
+@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@
++policy_module(qcom_bootprof, 1.0)
++
++########################################
++#
++# BOOTPROF: allow systemd (init_t) and udev (udev_t) to write ftrace
++# trace_marker under tracefs, for boot-time marker instrumentation.
++# Debug-only; drop this module to restore stock policy.
++#
++
++gen_require(`
++	type init_t;
++	type udev_t;
++	type tracefs_t;
++')
++
++# Write markers to /sys/kernel/tracing/trace_marker.
++allow init_t tracefs_t:file { open write getattr append };
++allow init_t tracefs_t:dir { search read getattr open };
++
++allow udev_t tracefs_t:file { open write getattr append };
++allow udev_t tracefs_t:dir { search read getattr open };
diff --git a/dynamic-layers/selinux/recipes-security/refpolicy/refpolicy-targeted_git.bbappend b/dynamic-layers/selinux/recipes-security/refpolicy/refpolicy-targeted_git.bbappend
index baa5a242..3f663525 100644
--- a/dynamic-layers/selinux/recipes-security/refpolicy/refpolicy-targeted_git.bbappend
+++ b/dynamic-layers/selinux/recipes-security/refpolicy/refpolicy-targeted_git.bbappend
@@ -2,4 +2,5 @@ FILESEXTRAPATHS:prepend := "${THISDIR}/${PN}:"
 
 SRC_URI:append:qcom = " \
     file://0001-Add-SELinux-policy-for-nhx.sh.patch \
+    file://0002-Add-SELinux-policy-for-bootprof-tracefs.patch \
 "
